From f33c756054fb765c421e0977654bbf3ea662f5f4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium Build <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 15:01:17 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 01/14] chronium: add --fingerprint-profile switch and
 FingerprintProfile singleton

Adds a new browser-process command-line switch "fingerprint-profile"
that takes a path to a JSON file. At startup
(PreCreateThreadsImpl), the JSON is loaded into a NoDestructor
singleton chronium::FingerprintProfile.

This is the plumbing foundation for all later fingerprint patches
(canvas noise, WebGL spoof, navigator override, etc.). Each later
patch will read its config from FingerprintProfile::GetInstance().

When the switch is absent or the file is missing/malformed, the
singleton stays in 'no profile' mode and downstream patches must
fall back to default (real) behavior.

Files touched:
- chrome/browser/fingerprint/fingerprint_profile.{h,cc}  (new)
- chrome/common/chrome_switches.{h,cc}                   (declare/define switch)
- chrome/browser/chrome_browser_main.cc                  (load in PreCreateThreadsImpl)
- chrome/browser/BUILD.gn                                (build the new sources)

Verified: 'chronium' launches, logs 'Loaded fingerprint profile from
...' to stderr when the switch is passed. UI boots normally.
